{{italic title}}
'''''Accra Daily Mail''''' was an [[English-language]] daily newspaper from [[Accra]], [[Ghana]]. The paper, which is privately owned, was started in 1998.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ghana. Country reports|url=http://downloads.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/trust/pdf/AMDI/ghana/amdi_ghana7_newspapers.pdf|accessdate=18 June 2015|work=BBC}}</ref> The daily ceased publication in January 2009 due to financial problems.<ref>{{cite news|title=Financial crisis crumpling Ghana newspapers|url=https://kentgh.wordpress.com/2009/03/05/financial-crisis-crumpling-ghana-newspapers/|accessdate=18 June 2015|work=Kent's Diaries|date=5 March 2009}}</ref> In April 2009 the paper was relaunched with the name ''The Mail''.<ref name=biz>{{cite news|title=The Accra Daily Mail relaunches in Ghana|url=http://www.bizcommunity.com.gh/Article/83/90/35094.html|accessdate=18 June 2015|work=Biz Community|date=17 April 2009}}</ref> Its frequency was also changed to biweekly.<ref name=biz/>

