The '''Federación Andaluza de Fútbol''' (FAF) is the football association responsible for all competitions of any form of football developed in [[Andalusia]]. It is integrated into the [[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] and its headquarters are located in [[Seville]] and has offices in the capitals of the provinces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.faf.es/reglamen/pdf/estatuto.pdf |title=Federación andaluza de fútbol, estatutos |publisher=Federación andaluza de fútbol |accessdate=27 October 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110907110017/http://www.faf.es/reglamen/pdf/estatuto.pdf |archivedate=7 September 2011 }}</ref>
It originated in the so-called ''Federación Novena de Football Clubes'' headed by Francisco Javier Alba and founded on 22 February 1915, and was the organizer of the various football events occurring in the community after the boom of the game in the second decade of the 20th century. It has been called ''Federación Regional Sur'' since 1916 and took its current name on 17 March 1950.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.faf.es/presiden/fundacion.htm |title=Federación andaluza de fútbol, fundación |publisher=Federación andaluza de fútbol |accessdate=27 October 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007071125/http://www.faf.es/presiden/fundacion.htm |archivedate=7 October 2011 }}</ref>
