{{Coord|43|46|55.05|N|11|14|53.89|E|type:landmark|display=title}} {{Expand Italian|Fortezza da Basso|date=December 2015}} [[Image:Fortezza da basso, ingresso 01.JPG|thumb|Entrance to the fort]] '''Fortezza da Basso''' is a [[fort]] inserted in the fourteenth century walls of [[Florence]]. Its official name is the Fortress of [[Saint John the Baptist]] ('''Fortezza di San Giovanni Battista'''). In modern times it is home to numerous conferences, concerts and national and international exhibitions, such as [[Pitti Immagine]]. Its total area is nearly 100,000 square meters.
==Construction== Fortezza da Basso was designed by [[Antonio da Sangallo the Younger]] for [[Alessandro de' Medici, Duke of Florence]], also called ''The [[Moors|Moor]]'', and built between 1534 and 1537.<ref>[http://www.firenzefiera.it/en/our-venues/fortezza-da-basso Fortezza da Basso] Firenze Fiera</ref> It is the largest historical monument of [[Florence]].
==Images== <gallery> Image:Fotezza da basso 21 polveriera.JPG Image:Fotezza da basso 01.JPG Image:Fotezza da basso 17 padiglione spadolini interno.JPG Image:Fontana Fortezza da Basso.JPG Image:Fotezza da basso 10.JPG </gallery>
