{{Politics of Gibraltar}}

'''[[General election]]s were held in [[Gibraltar]] in May 1996'''. They were won by [[Peter Caruana|Peter Caruana's]] [[Gibraltar Social Democrats]] (GSD), who took over 50% of the popular vote and eight of the 15 contested seats, defeating incumbent [[Joe Bossano|Joe Bossano's]] [[Gibraltar Socialist Labour Party]].

