{{Infobox TV channel|name=JTV Ethiopia|logofile=JTV_Ethiopia.jpg|logosize=|launch=2016|closed date=|picture format=[[576i]] ([[high-definition television|HDTV]]), [[Aspect ratio (image)#16:9 standard|16:9]])|share=10%|share as of={{as of|March 2017|}}|network=Television network|owner=Josef Gebre|slogan=ኢትዮዽያዊነት መልካምነት "Ethiopian Kindness"|country=[[Ethiopia]]|former names=JTV|sister names=|timeshift names=|web=http://jtvethiopia.com|Watch Live=|sat serv 1=[[Nilesat]] 7°W|sat chan 1=11595 H 27500 3/4|sat serv 2=|sat chan 2=}}
'''JTV Ethiopia''' is a private commercial television channel operating in Ethiopia. It is based in [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], Arizona, [[United States|U.S]] and was launched in 2016 on [[Nilesat]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://addisfortune.net/articles/new-channels-abundance-increases-competition-for-tv-ad-revenues/|title=New Channels Abundance Increases Competition for TV Ad Revenues|last=Yoseph|first=Nardos|date=Aug 2, 2016|work=Addis Fortune|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jtvethiopia.com/about-us/|title=About Us|last=|first=|date=|website=JTV Ethiopia|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
== History == The channel was started and named after the singer and talk show host Yosef Gebre (known as Jossy) who previously hosted his talk show ''Jossy in Z House'' on [[EBS TV (Ethiopia)|EBS TV]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201508241800.html|title=Leza Award Nominees Revealed|last=Makonnen|first=Meherete-Selassie|date=August 22, 2015|work=All Africa|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> After an alleged dispute with EBS TV in 2014,{{cn|reason=who?|date=February 2018}} Yosef took his talk show off the channel and started his own channel which later became JTV Ethiopia. The channel has correspondents and studios in [[Addis Ababa]], Ethiopia.{{cn|reason=who?|date=February 2018}} The channel obtained a license to broadcast in Ethiopia in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://addisfortune.net/articles/nahoo-ebs-secure-local-licenses-ending-debate/|title=Nahoo, EBS Secure Local Licenses Ending Debate|last=HAILEMARIAM|first=BERHANE|date=April 15, 2018|work=Addis Fortune|access-date=}}</ref>
== Programming == * ''Jossy in Z House'' * ''Hello Tech'' * ''Gash Chewata'' * ''JTV Sports'' * ''Travel Ethiopia'' * ''Habesha Weekly''
