{{Infobox language family |name=Kongo |altname=Kikongo |ethnicity= |region= |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone H|Zone H.10]]) |fam6=[[Kongo–Yaka–Sira]]? |glotto=none<!--core1256 is not a good match--> }}
The '''Kongo languages''' are a clade of [[Bantu language]]s coded Zone H.10 in Guthrie's classification. According to Nurse & Philippson (2003), apart from [[Kunyi language|Kunyi]], [[Suundi language|Suundi]] and [[Vili language|Vili]] the languages form a valid node. They are: : [[Bembe language (Kibembe)|Beembe]] (Pangwa, Doondo, Kamba, Hangala), [[Ndingi language|Ndingi]], [[Mboka language|Mboka]], [[Kongo language|Kongo]], [[Western Kongo]], [[Laari language|Laari]] (Laadi), [[Yombe language|Yombe]]
==References== *Nurse & Philippson (2003), ''The Bantu Languages.''
