{{Infobox film | name = Les Anges de Satan (Satan’s Angels) | image = | caption = | director = Ahmed Boulane | producer = Boulane O’Byrne Prod., Cinédina Studios | writer = | starring = Mansour Badri, Amal Chabli, Younes Megri, Driss Roukhe, [[Amal Ayouch]], Rafik Boubker, Amina Rachid | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2007}} | runtime = 85 minutes | country = Morocco | language = | budget = | gross = | screenplay = Ahmed Boulane | cinematography = Serge Hannecart | sound = Mohamed Bounouar | editing = Arbi Ben Ali | music = Joël Pellegrini }} '''''Les Anges de Satan''''' is a 2007 [[Morocco|Moroccan]] film, directed by [[Ahmed Boulane]].
== Synopsis == ''Les Anges de Satan'' is the story of fourteen young hard rock musicians who are arrested and sentenced to three months to one year in jail for "shaking the foundations of Islam" and "Satanism" after a surrealistic trial. Society and the media mobilize to free them…
