[[Category:National libraries|Somalia]] [[Category:Libraries in Somalia]] [[Category:Mogadishu]] [[Category:1975 establishments in Somalia]] [[Category:Libraries established in 1975]]

'''[[Polygamy]]''' is legal in '''[[Equatorial Guinea]]''' and such unions are recognized by the nation's system of [[customary law]]; which provides those under such unions with exactly the same rights found under the country's [[civil marriage]]s. However, unlike civil marriage, customary marriages do not grant men and women equal rights; with all of the rights falling into the husband's hands.<ref>[http://www.uoregon.edu/~aweiss/intl421_521/CEDAW_Report_West_Africa.pdf]</ref><ref>[http://www.law.emory.edu/ifl/region/westafrica.html West Africa]</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uneca.org/adfvi/documents/ADFVI_Progress_Report_ENG.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-02-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090204224800/http://www.uneca.org/adfvi/documents/ADFVI_Progress_Report_ENG.pdf |archivedate=2009-02-04 |df= }}</ref>

