{{otheruses|Tripoli (disambiguation)}}
'''Tripolis''' ({{lang-el|Τρίπολις}}; meaning "three cities") was a district in ancient [[Tripolitania]] (an expanded area based on the Tripolis), now in [[Libya]], along the [[Mediterranean Sea|Mediterranean]] between the [[Sabrata (river)|Sabrata]] and [[Cinyps]] rivers, and comprising the three cities of [[Oea]], [[Sabratha]], and [[Leptis Magna]].

